Systema is a Russian martial art which continues the traditional fighting styles of Russia dating back to the 10th Century. </p>
    				<p>Historically, the people of Russia had to defend their homeland from a variety of invaders, all using their own distinct 
   		 		styles of fighting and weapons, as well as their own approach to warfare. Because of the vast size of the 
    				country, Russia has a wide range of terrains and climates, so those fighting had to be versatile and adaptable not only 
    				to the different styles and strategies of their attackers, but also to the wide variation in the natural environment.